The paper deals with secure split manufacturing, which is a technique to defend against malicious activities in the fabrication process of integrated circuits. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and hardware design and analysis (cs.AR). The paper also discusses layout techniques, which are related to electronic design automation (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper proposes a theoretical framework for quantifying the resilience of layouts, which is related to information theory (cs.IT).
